{{Quote|I remember the ships. The last stand of the Republic. The tattered remnants of our fleet, the largest we could gather, but it was damaged, weakened and vulnerable. The Mandalorians couldn't resist. They tore into us like beasts, shredding our ships to scrap as we fought back.|[[Bao-Dur]]|<ref name="KOTOR 2" />}}
The [[Standard year/Legends|year]] '''3960 before the Battle of Yavin (BBY)''', as it was known in the [[Galactic Standard Calendar]], saw the end of the [[Mandalorian Wars]] between the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] and the [[Mandalorian/Legends|Mandalorian]] warrior culture. Also known as the year '''32,503 After the Tho Yor Arrival (TYA)''', the year '''307 before the Treaty of Coruscant (BTC)''', the year '''2,960 before the Ruusan Reformation''', and the year '''3,925 before the Great ReSynchronization (BrS)''', the year included the [[Battle of Malachor V]], where Revan defeated [[Mandalore the Ultimate]] in single combat and the activation of the [[Mass Shadow Generator/Legends|Mass Shadow Generator]] destroyed most of the Mandalorian forces. From the dying Mandalore, Revan discovered the Mandalorians had been influenced by the [[Sith/Legends|Sith]], and his search for answers led to his and Malak's corruption at the hands of the [[Tenebrae|Sith Emperor]]. The year's events had powerful ramifications, as they led to the [[Jedi Civil War]] of [[3959 BBY|3959]]-[[3956 BBY]] and the later [[Dark Wars]].

==Events==
{{Quote|It wasn't supposed to end like this. They promised me victory. Only now do I see how I was betrayed.|Mandalore the Ultimate|<ref name="Revan" />}}
*The [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] scores a victory against the [[Mandalorian/Legends|Mandalorians]] in a [[Second battle of Onderon (Mandalorian Wars)|battle]] at the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Onderon/Legends|Onderon]],<ref name="Onderon">{{Wizards|url=default.asp?x=starwars/article/Onderon|text=Onderon Cutoff|int=Onderon Cutoff}}</ref> and another [[Second battle of the Lianna system|victory]] in the [[Lianna system/Legends|Lianna system]].<ref name="Atlas">''[[The Essential Atlas]]''</ref>
*The [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]] [[Revan/Legends|Revan]] lures the Mandalorians into a final showdown at the planet [[Malachor V]], and he challenges their leader [[Mandalore the Ultimate]] to a duel to the [[Death/Legends|death]] while the [[Battle of Malachor V]] rages. Revan wins their duel, killing Mandalore and taking his [[Mandalore's Mask|mask]], though he learns that the [[Mandalorian Wars]] were orchestrated by the [[Sith/Legends|Sith]].<ref name="Revan" />
*The battle, and the Mandalorian Wars as a whole,<ref name="Chronicles">{{LucasArts|url=games/swkotor_sithlords|text=''Chronicles of the Old Republic''|int=Chronicles of the Old Republic}}</ref> is brought to end when Revan's lieutenant,<ref name="KOTOR 2" /> the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Meetra Surik]],<ref name="Revan" /> activates the [[Mass Shadow Generator/Legends|Mass Shadow Generator]] on Revan's orders and destroys the Mandalorian fleets along with a large number of Republic forces and Jedi&mdash;[[Arren Kae]] among them<ref name="KOTOR 2" />
*After witnessing the devastation caused by the weapon and feeling and the deaths through [[The Force/Legends|the Force]], Surik [[Sever Force/Legends|severs]] her connection to the Force.<ref name="Campaign" />
*Revan and [[Darth Malak|Malak]] depart into the [[Unknown Regions/Legends|Unknown Regions]] with a third of the Republic fleet,<ref name="KOTOR">''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic]]''</ref> though they travel alone to follow Mandalore's instructions to [[Rekkiad]]. There, they discover the [[Dramath the Second's tomb|tomb]] of [[Dramath the Second]], and Revan leaves Mandalore's Mask in the tomb before they leave for [[Nathema]].<ref name="Revan" />
*After witnessing the devastation on Nathema, Revan and Malak follow the [[Sith Empire (Post–Great Hyperspace War)|Sith survivors]] to [[Dromund Kaas/Legends|Dromund Kaas]]. After [[Mission to Dromund Kaas|months of posing undercover]] as [[Mercenary/Legends|mercenaries]], they are lured into a trap where they are [[Qâzoi Kyantuska|mentally dominated]] by the [[Tenebrae|Sith Emperor]] and turned to the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side of the Force]]. As [[Dark Lord of the Sith/Legends|Dark Lords of the Sith]], they are ordered to locate the [[Rakata/Legends|Rakatan]] [[Space station/Legends|space station]] known as the [[Star Forge]].<ref name="Encyclopedia">''[[Star Wars: The Old Republic Encyclopedia]]''</ref>
*Darth Revan and his apprentice, Darth Malak, crash land on [[Lehon/Legends|Lehon]]. They gain access to the Rakatan [[Temple of the Ancients]] which, in turn, grants them access to the Star Forge.<ref name="KOTOR" />
*The [[Night of the Upside-Down Meteor]] occurs, where [[Grand Lord]] [[Lillia Venn]] of the [[Lost Tribe of Sith]] attempts to escape the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Kesh/Legends|Kesh]] in an [[Aurek-class tactical strikefighter|''Aurek''-class tactical starfighter]] belonging to the Jedi [[Jelph Marrian]]. However, she is killed with her subordinates [[Sawj Luzo|Sawj]] and [[Flen Luzo]] when the fighter explodes thanks to the explosives that Marrian placed inside.<ref name="Sentinel" />

